               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1766" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1766" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1766" type="surname" value="LYON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1766" type="given" value="JOHN ANDREW"></interp>JOHN ANDREW LYON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the brother of Washington Lyon, who lives with me in the Kent-road. On the 17th of January, at seven o'clock in the morning, I saw the parlour window open—my attention was drawn to it by my mother, who was the first up—the coats and a cloak were gone from the passage—there had been one coat of mine and two of my brother's—the cloak had been taken from there, but was left in the parlour, near the window, which had been got up by some force—we went out, and saw a strange footmark on the garden-beds—this is my coat, and these are my brother's.</p>
